        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Malachi 2:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The אהל is not, as one might suppose, the holy tent or tabernacle, that he has desecrated by making it the lurking-place of the betrayer (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 21:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), which would have been expressed by מאהלו, but his own dwelling. God will pull him, the lofty and imperious one, down (נתץ, like a tower perhaps, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 8:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 26:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") from his position of honour and his prosperity, and drag him forth out of his habitation, much as one rakes a coal from the hearth (חתה Biblical and Talmudic in this sense), and tear him out of this his home (נסח, cf. נתק, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 18:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and remove him far away (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), because he has betrayed the homeless fugitive; and will root him out of the land of the living, because he has destroyed the priests of God (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 22:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It then proceeds in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 52:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " very much like ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 40:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 40:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", just as the figure of the razor also coincides with Psalms belonging to exactly the same period (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 51:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
