      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") reprobates the low malignant joy that glories at the overthrow of one's enemy. By ויּבטח the former trust in mammon on the part of the man who is overtaken by punishment is set forth as a consequence of his refusal to put trust in God, in Him who is the true מעוז  equals  Arab. m‛âḏ, hiding-place or place of protection (vid., on 31;3, ",
